MacroMolecule.Protein.AtomIterator

public MacroMolecule.Protein.AtomIterator(int fromResidue,
                                          int toResidue)
Creates an iterator that enumerates all atoms of the polymer between the specified range of residue numbers. Hydrogen atoms are not listed unless setIncludeHydrogens( true ) is called.

Parameters:
fromResidue - residue number of the first residue listed
toResidue - residue number of the last residue listed
Method Detail

getSecondaryStructureType

public int getSecondaryStructureType()
Description copied from interface: MoleculeIterators.AtomIteratorInterface
Gets the type of the secondary structure element which the current atom belongs to. This method makes sense for MacroMolecule.Protein atoms only. It is declared here in order to support higher level polymorphism.
